{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01USqAJkrBbDWiLXKtrdQMcM","type":"tool_result","content":"_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-architecture-v3.md:221:### Story 12-3: Move business logic from status.ts command to status module\n_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-multi-framework.md:65:- NFR6: Driver health check (all drivers in workflow) must complete within 5 seconds at workflow start\n_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-multi-framework.md:145:Users can dispatch tasks to Codex CLI and OpenCode CLI. Both drivers implement AgentDriver, parse CLI output to StreamEvent, and handle health checks.\n_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-multi-framework.md:281:Users can dispatch tasks to Codex CLI and OpenCode CLI with full health checking.\n_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-multi-framework.md:324:I want all referenced drivers health-checked before any task executes,\n_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-multi-framework.md:332:**And** all health checks complete within 5 seconds total (NFR6)\n_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-archive-v1.md:165:FR29: Epic 4 — session start health check\n_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-archive-v1.md:516:**When** a health check is performed (via hook or `codeharness status --check-docker`)\n_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-archive-v1.md:974:**Then** the SessionStart hook fires (session flags reset, health check)\n_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-archive-v1.md:1149:**When** health checks execute\n_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-archive-v1.md:1449:**Then** Docker health check is skipped for remote backends\n_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-archive-v1.md:1450:**And** connectivity to remote endpoints is verified via HTTP health check instead\n_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-archive-v1.md:1822:- 12-3: Unverifiable AC detection & escalation\n_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture.md:53:3. **Docker lifecycle** — Start, stop, health check. Must handle: not installed (skip if observability OFF), not started, started, crashed, user stopped manually. CLI owns this.\n_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/sprint-change-proposal-2026-03-16-verification-integrity.md:41:| 12-3: Unverifiable AC Detection | (new) | AC classification, verifier escalation, harness-run halt on integration-required ACs |\n_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd.md:111:| Driver health check | At workflow start, verify all referenced drivers are installed and authenticated |\n_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd.md:358:- **Driver health check at startup** — before any task dispatches, engine verifies each referenced driver's CLI is installed and authenticated\n_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd.md:446:- NFR6: Driver health check (all drivers in workflow) must complete within 5 seconds at workflow start\n_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/product-brief-operational-excellence-2026-03-19.md:40:2. **No continuous compliance.** `codeharness onboard` runs once during setup. After that, the project drifts — tests get skipped, docs go stale, observability degrades. There's no \"run the full health check again\" command.\n_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-multi-framework.md:28:18 NFRs across performance (driver spawn <3s, TUI update <500ms, health check <5s), integration (pinned CLI versions, backward-compatible schema, no plugin modifications), and reliability (crash detection <5s, atomic contract writes, idempotent re-runs). Single-user local CLI — no scalability or availability requirements.\n_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-multi-framework.md:429:driver-factory → get driver by name → driver.healthCheck()\n_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-v3.md:292:**Decision:** `codeharness init` asks for backend choice. Stored in state. All query builders and health checks dispatch on backend type."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01Cc3NEnB4Yfzm2hoyASCyJg","session_id":"b101ea9e-2f9e-4377-9c5a-f109fa318b32","uuid":"ed112572-a345-4aef-85f7-072ef3c4b6bb",