{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01SyMuA2ThuXEZDyzY9QCZQP","type":"tool_result","content":"444-- NFR4: Output contract serialization/deserialization must complete within 1 second for contracts up to 1MB\n445-- NFR5: TUI render loop must maintain 15 FPS maximum without CPU spikes during active stream parsing\n446:- NFR6: Driver health check (all drivers in workflow) must complete within 5 seconds at workflow start\n447-\n448-### Integration\n--\n457-### Reliability\n458-\n459:- NFR13: If a driver process crashes mid-task, the engine must detect it within 5 seconds, report the failure, and allow retry\n460-- NFR14: If a driver's CLI output format is unparseable, the engine must surface the raw output for debugging — not silently drop it\n461-- NFR15: Output contract files must survive engine crashes — written atomically (write-then-rename) so partial writes don't corrupt cross-framework state"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01Cc3NEnB4Yfzm2hoyASCyJg","session_id":"b101ea9e-2f9e-4377-9c5a-f109fa318b32","uuid":"c86db6c7-68ce-443b-817c-494ca5b7ccd2","timestamp":"2026-04-03T09:38:47.632Z"}
