{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01J1hA6EdKQNp4qhAx3VLe1g","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\n\n## Summary\n\nImplemented Story 12-3: Driver Health Check at Workflow Start.\n\n**Files modified:**\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/workflow-engine.ts` — Added `checkDriverHealth()` exported function (lines ~730-788) and integrated it into `executeWorkflow()` between state initialization and work item loading\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/__tests__/workflow-engine.test.ts` — Updated `healthCheck` mock to return `{ available: true, authenticated: true, version: '1.0.0' }` and fixed one assertion for `mockGetDriver` call count (2 -> 3)\n\n**File created:**\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/__tests__/driver-health-check.test.ts` — 10 new tests covering all acceptance criteria\n\n**Implementation details:**\n- `checkDriverHealth(workflow, timeoutMs?)` collects unique driver names from tasks (defaulting to `claude-code`), deduplicates via `Set`, resolves each via `getDriver()`, runs all `healthCheck()` concurrently via `Promise.all()`, and races against a 5-second timeout via `Promise.race()`\n- On failure: throws with all failing driver names and error messages\n- On timeout: throws with timeout duration and driver list\n- Integration in `executeWorkflow()`: placed after early exit for completed workflows, before work item loading. On failure, sets `phase: 'failed'` and returns `success: false` with a `HEALTH_CHECK` error\n\n**Verification:** `npm run build` — 0 errors. `npm run test:unit` — 4488 passed, 0 failed, 167 files.\n\n## Session Issues\n\n- **Workaround applied:** Added optional `timeoutMs` parameter to `checkDriverHealth()` to make the timeout test work with real timers instead of fake timers. Fake timers caused unhandled rejection warnings from Vitest because `Promise.race` with `setTimeout` and a never-resolving health check resulted in the throw happening in a microtask that Vitest's rejection handler caught before the test's `await` could handle it. The optional parameter is a clean solution (defaults to 5000ms in production) but was not in the original spec.\n- **Existing test impact:** Had to update the `healthCheck` mock in `workflow-engine.test.ts` to return a valid `DriverHealth` object (was returning `undefined`). Also updated one assertion that counted `mockGetDriver` calls (now +1 for health check). Both are expected regressions from adding pre-flight health checks.\n- **Code quality concern:** The `setTimeout` in `checkDriverHealth` is not cleared after `Promise.all` resolves. If health checks complete quickly, the timer still fires after 5 seconds (harmlessly resolving a detached promise). This is standard `Promise.race` behavior but could be cleaned up with `AbortController` or manual timer cleanup for tidiness.\n\n## Token Report\n\n- Total tool calls: 19\n- By tool: Bash: 8, Read: 7, Edit: 7, Grep: 2, Write: 1, Glob: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs (top 3 by line count): `npm run test:unit` (~30 lines each, run 2x), `npm run build` (~20 lines)\n- Files read: 6 unique, 10 total reads\n  - `workflow-engine.test.ts` read 4x (initial, mocks section, failing test area x2)\n  - `workflow-engine.ts` read 3x (full file, import section, health check area)\n- Redundant operations: One `npm run build` call could have been skipped (ran before and after tests, both passed). Two reads of `workflow-engine.ts` partial sections could have been combined."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: acf238a32c3f4bf56 (use SendMessage with to: 'acf238a32c3f4bf56' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 64658\ntool_uses: 46\nduration_ms: 352459</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b101ea9e-2f9e-4377-9c5a-f109fa318b32","uuid":"62b3588a-2d87-4343-874e-1747518ecd7c","timestamp":"2026-04-03T09:46:47.385Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Run /bmad-dev-story for the story at _bmad-output/i