{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Pu3wXi4pA6EPLQcEQK8Uxb","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\n\n## Review Summary\n\n**Story:** 12-3-driver-health-check-at-workflow-start\n**Story Status:** verifying\n**Issues Found:** 1 High, 4 Medium, 1 Low\n**Issues Fixed:** 1 High, 3 Medium (4 total)\n**Build:** 0 TypeScript errors\n**Tests:** 123 passed (112 existing + 11 health check), 0 failed\n**Coverage:** 96.79% overall, all 169 files above 80% floor\n\n### Fixes Applied\n\n1. **HIGH — Timer leak on success path.** `setTimeout` timer was never cleared when health checks completed before timeout. Added `clearTimeout(timer!)` on the success path to prevent the timer from keeping the Node process alive unnecessarily.\n\n2. **MEDIUM — Inaccurate timeout error message (AC #6).** The timeout error previously listed ALL driver names regardless of which ones responded. Now tracks which drivers responded via a `responded` Set, and reports only the pending drivers in the error message.\n\n3. **MEDIUM — Double invocation in test.** The \"throws when one driver fails\" test called `checkDriverHealth` twice (once per `rejects.toThrow` assertion), doubling mock calls. Refactored to catch once and assert on the error object.\n\n4. **MEDIUM — Missing test for AC #6 specificity.** Added test \"timeout error reports only drivers that did not respond\" verifying that when one driver responds and another hangs, the error message names only the hanging driver.\n\n---\n\n## Session Issues\n\n**Bugs found:**\n- HIGH: Timer leak — `setTimeout` never cleared on success path in `checkDriverHealth()`. Fixed.\n- MEDIUM: Timeout error reports all drivers instead of only non-responding ones (AC #6 violation). Fixed.\n- MEDIUM: Test calls `checkDriverHealth` twice unnecessarily (double mock invocation). Fixed.\n\n**Code quality issues found but NOT fixed (LOW):**\n- LOW: `HealthResult` type defined inline in function body rather than at module scope. Cosmetic — left as-is since it's function-scoped and clear.\n\n**Coverage gaps:**\n- None. 96.79% overall, all files above 80% floor. Health check function is fully covered by 11 tests.\n\n**Architecture concerns:**\n- None. Implementation follows the existing driver factory pattern correctly. The `checkDriverHealth` function is well-isolated and testable.\n\n**Items sent back for re-development:**\n- None. All HIGH and MEDIUM issues were fixed in this review.\n\n## Token Report\n\n- Total tool calls: 21\n- By tool: Bash: 10, Read: 6, Edit: 4, Grep: 2, Glob: 1, Skill: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs (top 3 by line count): `git diff -- src/lib/workflow-engine.ts` (~70 lines), `git diff -- src/lib/__tests__/workflow-engine.test.ts` (~25 lines), `git status --porcelain` (~17 lines)\n- Files read: 8 unique, 9 total reads (no file read 3+ times)\n- Redundant operations: none"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: ac12be8d7d6f711a9 (use SendMessage with to: 'ac12be8d7d6f711a9' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 55306\ntool_uses: 31\nduration_ms: 153112</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b101ea9e-2f9e-4377-9c5a-f109fa318b32","uuid":"6a68778a-35a0-44df-ad93-885729a15257","timestamp":"2026-04-03T09:49:43.719Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Run /bmad-code-review for the story at _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/12-3-driver-health-check-at-workflow-start.md — perform adversarial review, fix all HIGH and MEDIUM issues found. After fixing, run `codeharness coverage --min-file 80` and ensure all files pass the per-file floor and the overall 90% target. Update the story status to `verifying` when all issues are fixed and coverage passes. Do NOT ask the user any questions — proceed autonomously. Do NOT run git commit. Do NOT run git add. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.\n\nMANDATORY — End your response with a `## Session Issues` section listing:\n- Bugs found and their severity (HIGH/MEDIUM/LOW with brief description)\n- Code