{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Umjmsf1uXzE9ujgPxKZamM","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Verification Proof: Story 12-3 — Driver Health Check at Workflow Start\n2\t\n3\t**Story:** `_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/12-3-driver-health-check-at-workflow-start.md`\n4\t**Verification Tier:** test-provable\n5\t**Date:** 2026-04-03\n6\t**Verifier:** Claude Opus 4.6 (1M context)\n7\t\n8\t## Build & Test Summary\n9\t\n10\t| Check | Result | Detail |\n11\t|-------|--------|--------|\n12\t| `npm run build` | PASS | 0 TypeScript errors, build success |\n13\t| `npm run test:unit` | PASS | 4489 passed, 0 failed, 167 test files |\n14\t| `npm run lint` | PASS (pre-existing) | 1 error (pre-existing `require-yield` in `workflow-engine.test.ts:154`, unrelated), 52 warnings |\n15\t| `npm run test:coverage` | Not run | Not required for test-provable tier |\n16\t\n17\t## Acceptance Criteria Verification\n18\t\n19\t### AC 1: Health checks called on every unique driver before task execution\n20\t**Result:** PASS\n21\t- **Evidence (code):** `checkDriverHealth()` exported at `src/lib/workflow-engine.ts:742`, collects unique driver names via `Set<string>` from `workflow.tasks`, calls `getDriver(name)` and `driver.healthCheck()` for each.\n22\t- **Evidence (test):** `succeeds when multiple unique drivers all pass` — PASSED\n23\t- **Evidence (test):** `deduplicates drivers — healthCheck called once per unique driver` — PASSED\n24\t- **Evidence (integration):** `checkDriverHealth(config.workflow)` called in `executeWorkflow()` at line 838, before work item loading.\n25\t\n26\t### AC 2: All drivers pass — workflow proceeds normally\n27\t**Result:** PASS\n28\t- **Evidence (code):** `checkDriverHealth()` returns `void` on success (line 794), no error thrown.\n29\t- **Evidence (test):** `succeeds when a single driver passes health check` — PASSED\n30\t- **Evidence (test):** `proceeds normally when all health checks pass` — PASSED\n31\t\n32\t### AC 3: One or more drivers fail — engine aborts with error listing ALL failures\n33\t**Result:** PASS\n34\t- **Evidence (code):** Lines 788-794 collect all failures, build error message with driver name and error field for each.\n35\t- **Evidence (test):** `throws when one driver fails, listing the failing driver and error` — PASSED\n36\t- **Evidence (test):** `throws listing ALL failing drivers when multiple fail` — PASSED\n37\t- **Evidence (integration):** `aborts with success=false when health check fails` — PASSED; returns `success: false` with `phase: 'failed'`.\n38\t\n39\t### AC 4: Default driver (claude-code) used when task has no driver field\n40\t**Result:** PASS\n41\t- **Evidence (code):** Line 746: `task.driver ?? 'claude-code'`\n42\t- **Evidence (test):** `defaults to claude-code when task has no driver field` — PASSED\n43\t\n44\t### AC 5: Health checks run concurrently via Promise.all with 5s timeout\n45\t**Result:** PASS\n46\t- **Evidence (code):** Line 758: `Promise.all([...drivers.entries()].map(...))` for concurrency. Line 773: `Promise.race([healthChecks, timeoutPromise])` with 5000ms default (line 731).\n47\t- **Evidence (test):** `throws on timeout when health check hangs` — PASSED (uses reduced timeout for test speed)\n48\t\n49\t### AC 6: Timeout aborts with error listing non-responding drivers\n50\t**Result:** PASS\n51\t- **Evidence (code):** Lines 775-781: On timeout, filters `driverNames` against `responded` set, reports only pending drivers.\n52\t- **Evidence (test):** `timeout error reports only drivers that did not respond` — PASSED\n53\t\n54\t### AC 7: Completed workflow skips health checks entirely\n55\t**Result:** PASS\n56\t- **Evidence (code):** Lines 818-826: Early exit for `state.phase === 'completed'` returns before `checkDriverHealth()` call at line 838.\n57\t- **Evidence (test):** `skips health checks for completed workflows` — PASSED\n58\t\n59\t### AC 8: Driver names collected from workflow tasks with deduplication\n60\t**Result:** PASS\n61\t- **Evidence (code):** Lines 744-747: Iterates `Object.values(workflow.tasks)`, reads `task.driver` with default, adds to `Set<string>`, then calls `getDriver(name)`.\n62\t- **Evidence (test):** `deduplicates drivers — healthCheck called once per unique driver` — PASSED\n63\t\n64\t### AC 9: Build succeeds with zero errors, all tests pass\n65\t**Result:** PASS\n66\t- **Evidence:** `npm run build` — 0 errors. `npm run test:unit` — 4489 passed, 0 failed, 167 test files.\n67\t\n68\t## Files Verified\n69\t\n70\t| File | Exists | Role |\n71\t|------|--------|------|\n72\t| `src/lib/workflow-engine.ts` | Yes | `checkDriverHealth()` function + `executeWorkflow()` integration |\n73\t| `src/lib/__tests__/driver-health-check.test.ts` | Yes | 11 tests (8 unit + 3 integration) |\n74\t\n75\t## Test Names (all PASSED)\n76\t\n77\t1. `checkDriverHealth > succeeds when a single driver passes health check`\n78\t2. `checkDriverHealth > succeeds when multiple unique drivers all pass`\n79\t3. `checkDriverHealth > deduplicates drivers — healthCheck called once per unique driver`\n80\t4. `checkDriverHealth > throws when one driver fails, listing the failing driver and error`\n81\t5. `checkDriverHealth > throws listing ALL failing drivers when multiple fail`\n82\t6. `checkDriverHealth > defaults to claude-code when task has no driver field`\n83\t7. `checkDriverHealth > throws on timeout when health check hangs`\n84\t8. `checkDriverHealth > timeout error reports only drivers that did not respond`\n85\t9. `executeWorkflow — health check integration > skips health checks for completed workflows`\n86\t10. `executeWorkflow — health check integration > aborts with success=false when health check fails`\n87\t11. `executeWorkflow — health check integration > proceeds normally when all health checks pass`\n88\t\n89\t## Final Verdict\n90\t\n91\t**ALL_PASS (9/9 ACs)**\n92\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b101ea9e-2f9e-4377-9c5a-f109fa318b32","uuid":"c9f8d2b6-7b23-4e31-82d9-cdac20