quivalent cost this sprint\n   - Cost per phase (which phases are most expensive?)\n   - Cost per story (which stories cost the most and why?)\n   - Wasted spend (no-op sessions, failed verifications, retries)\n   - Cost optimization opportunities\n4. **What went well** — stories completed, bugs fixed, process improvements\n5. **What went wrong** — failures, blockers, stuck stories, wasted iterations\n6. **Lessons learned** — patterns to repeat or avoid\n7. **Action items** — concrete next steps\n\nWrite the retrospective to _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/session-retro-2026-04-03.md. If a session retro for today already exists, append to it with a `---` separator and timestamp.\n\nDo NOT ask the user any questions — proceed autonomously.\nDo NOT run git commit. Do NOT run git add. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.","subagent_type":"general-purpose"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":283,"cache_read_input_tokens":71969,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":283},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b101ea9e-2f9e-4377-9c5a-f109fa318b32","uuid":"b00b9679-5f9c-4999-8260-129b43c4eb30"}
