{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01KD2qWYZxv1F7JHdoatKbvP","type":"tool_result","content":"3191\t# Session Retrospective — 2026-04-03 (Session 9, Iteration 9)\n3192\t\n3193\t**Timestamp:** 2026-04-03T13:35 UTC+4\n3194\t**Session window:** ~13:15 to ~13:33 (approx. 18 minutes)\n3195\t**Sprint progress:** 36/47 stories done (76.6%), Epics 1-11 complete, Epic 12 at 2/3\n3196\t\n3197\t---\n3198\t\n3199\t## 1. Session Summary\n3200\t\n3201\t| Story | Phases Run | Outcome | Notes |\n3202\t|-------|-----------|---------|-------|\n3203\t| 12-2-opencode-driver-implementation | create-story, dev-story, code-review, verify | **Done** | Full lifecycle. 11/11 ACs passed. Commit `1ed6db3`. |\n3204\t\n3205\t**Net output:** 1 story completed and verified in a single iteration (~18 minutes). This is the fastest full-lifecycle story delivery in the project so far.\n3206\t\n3207\t---\n3208\t\n3209\t## 2. Issues Analysis\n3210\t\n3211\t### Issues Reported by Subagents\n3212\t\n3213\t| Phase | Severity | Issue | Impact |\n3214\t|-------|----------|-------|--------|\n3215\t| create-story | INFO | OpenCode CLI output format must be reverse-engineered; fixtures are plausible guesses | Low — gracefully handles command failure |\n3216\t| create-story | INFO | `opencode auth status` command is a guess | Low — healthCheck handles failure gracefully |\n3217\t| create-story | INFO | No `project-context.md` found (workflow references it) | None — no impact |\n3218\t| create-story | LOW | `classifyError` duplication between CodexDriver and OpenCodeDriver (~80 identical lines) | Technical debt — intentional per architecture decision |\n3219\t| code-review | LOW | Dead fixture files in `test/fixtures/drivers/opencode/*.txt` (tests use inline data) | Cleanup debt |\n3220\t| code-review | LOW | `console.debug` for unparseable lines instead of structured logger | Shared pattern across all drivers |\n3221\t| verify | MEDIUM | Stale AGENTS.md — `codeharness verify` fails on precondition for src/lib/agents/drivers module | Pre-existing debt, not story-related. 14th session flagging this. |\n3222\t| verify | LOW | Test count discrepancy: story changelog says 64, actual is 69 | Minor documentation drift |\n3223\t| verify | INFO | Branch coverage 96.03% — 4 uncovered branches at lines 149, 198, 306-307 | Acceptable — edge cases in parseLine and error catch |\n3224\t\n3225\t**No HIGH issues.** No bugs found by code-review requiring fixes. This is the first driver story to pass code-review with zero fixes needed.\n3226\t\n3227\t### Categorization\n3228\t\n3229\t- **Bugs found:** 0 (zero code-review fixes needed)\n3230\t- **Technical debt:** 2 (classifyError duplication, dead fixtures)\n3231\t- **Documentation debt:** 2 (AGENTS.md stale, test count discrepancy)\n3232\t- **Known unknowns:** 2 (OpenCode CLI output format, auth check command)\n3233\t\n3234\t---\n3235\t\n3236\t## 3. Cost Analysis\n3237\t\n3238\t### Session-Level Cost\n3239\t\n3240\tThe `codeharness stats` command is not available (no session-logs/ directory — this is tracked as action #45 from prior retro). Cost analysis uses the subagent token reports from the session issues log.\n3241\t\n3242\t### Subagent Tool Call Breakdown\n3243\t\n3244\t| Phase | Tool Calls | Bash | Read | Edit | Write | Grep | Glob | Skill | Unique Files |\n3245\t|-------|-----------|------|------|------|-------|------|------|-------|-------------|\n3246\t| create-story | 16 | 3 | 7 | 0 | 1 | 4 | 2 | 1 | 10 |\n3247\t| dev-story | 20 | 4 | 11 | 3 | 6 | 0 | 2 | 1 | 11 |\n3248\t| code-review | 12 | 3 | 7 | 1 | 0 | 1 | 3 | 1 | 8 |\n3249\t| verify | 11 | 7 | 3 | 0 | 1 | 0 | 0 | 0 | 3 |\n3250\t| **Total** | **59** | **17** | **28** | **4** | **8** | **5** | **7** | **3** | — |\n3251\t\n3252\t### Analysis\n3253\t\n3254\t- **No redundancy reported by any subagent.** All four phases reported \"No redundancy\" — zero repeated file reads, zero wasted Bash calls. This is a first.\n3255\t- **Read-heavy profile (47% of calls):** Expected — subagents need to read the existing CodexDriver, interface types, test patterns, and story spec.\n3256\t- **Low tool count overall (59 total):** Compare to story 12-1 (Codex driver) which was in the prior retro's session. The OpenCode driver benefited from the established pattern.\n3257\t- **Verify phase is Bash-heavy (7/11 calls):** Running test suites, coverage checks, and build verification. This is structurally correct.\n3258\t\n3259\t### Cumulative Cost Context (from cost-report.md)\n3260\t\n3261\tThe cumulative project cost report shows $202.85 across 1568 API calls and 49 stories ($3.46/story average). The verify phase dominates at 44.3% of total cost — this remains the most expensive phase and is the primary target for cost optimization.\n3262\t\n3263\t---\n3264\t\n3265\t## 4. What Went Well\n3266\t\n3267\t1. **Fastest full-lifecycle story:** ~18 minutes from create-story to verified-done. Previous fastest was ~25 minutes (story 12-1).\n3268\t2. **Zero code-review fixes:** First time a driver story passed code-review clean. The CodexDriver pattern established in 12-1 paid off — the template was followed precisely.\n3269\t3. **Zero redundancy across all subagents.** No repeated reads, no wasted operations. Subagents are staying focused.\n3270\t4. **All 11 ACs passed on first verify run.** No re-verification needed.\n3271\t5. **Pattern reuse worked.** The architecture decision to keep drivers as independent files with duplicated utility code (classifyError, etc.) made 12-2 a near-copy of 12-1, which is exactly the intent.\n3272\t6. **96.78% statement coverage, 96.03% branch coverage.** Well above the 80% floor.\n3273\t\n3274\t---\n3275\t\n3276\t## 5. What Went Wrong\n3277\t\n3278\t1. **AGENTS.md stale — 14th session.** This is now the longest-running unresolved action item in the project. `codeharness verify` fails its precondition check every single session because of this. It is noise that every verify subagent must work around.\n3279\t2. **`codeharness stats` still broken.** Action #45 from the prior retro remains open. No session-logs/ directory exists, so cost reporting depends on manual subagent token report aggregation.\n3280\t3. **classifyError duplication not extracted.** Action #41 from prior retro recommended extracting shared driver utilities before 12-2. This was not done. Now three drivers (claude-code, codex, opencode) have identical classifyError implementations.\n3281\t4. **Dead fixture files created.** create-story generated `test/fixtures/drivers/opencode/*.txt` but dev-story used inline test data instead. Minor waste.\n3282\t\n3283\t---\n3284\t\n3285\t## 6. Lessons Learned\n3286\t\n3287\t### Patterns to Repeat\n3288\t\n3289\t- **Template-driven driver stories work.** When the first driver (claude-code extraction in 10-3) establishes the pattern and the second (codex, 12-1) validates it, the third (opencode, 12-2) becomes near-mechanical. Keep this approach for future drivers.\n3290\t- **Inline test data over fixture files.** Both 12-1 and 12-2 used inline test data, which is faster to write and avoids dead fixture debt. Make this the standard for driver tests.\n3291\t- **Keeping subagent phases lean.** 59 total tool calls for a full lifecycle is efficient. The session issues log shows all phases reported zero redundancy.\n3292\t\n3293\t### Patterns to Avoid\n3294\t\n3295\t- **Skipping shared utility extraction.** The prior retro flagged this explicitly. Ignoring it means the debt grows with each new driver. Before 12-3 or any Epic 13+ work, extract `classifyError` and `NETWORK_CODES`.\n3296\t- **Creating fixture files that tests don't use.** The create-story phase should not generate fixture files unless the dev-story phase is guaranteed to use them.\n3297\t\n3298\t---\n3299\t\n3300\t## 7. Action Items\n3301\t\n3302\t### Carried Forward (Still Open)\n3303\t\n3304\t| # | Action | Priority | Status |\n3305\t|---|--------|----------|--------|\n3306\t| 3 | Fix AGENTS.md for all new modules | HIGH | Open — 14 sessions |\n3307\t| 37 | Fix epic numbering mismatch | MEDIUM | Open |\n3308\t| 41 | Extract `classifyError` + `NETWORK_CODES` to shared driver utility | HIGH | Open — now 3 drivers duplicated |\n3309\t| 42 | Validate Codex CLI NDJSON output against real CLI | MEDIUM | Backlog |\n3310\t| 45 | Fix `codeharness stats --save` — no session-logs directory | LOW | Open |\n3311\t\n3312\t### New This Session\n3313\t\n3314\t| # | Action | Priority | Owner |\n3315\t|---|--------|----------|-------|\n3316\t| 46 | Remove dead fixture files in `test/fixtures/drivers/opencode/` | LOW | Cleanup |\n3317\t| 47 | Standardize on inline test data for driver tests (update create-story template) | LOW | Process |\n3318\t\n3319\t### Priority Recommendations for Next Session\n3320\t\n3321\t1. **Story 12-3 (driver health check at workflow start)** — completes Epic 12. All three drivers are now implemented.\n3322\t2. **Extract shared driver utilities (action #41)** — before Epic 13 begins. Three duplicated implementations is the limit.\n3323\t3. **Fix AGENTS.md (action #3)** — 14 sessions. Just do it.\n3324\t4. **Epic 13 (output contracts)** — next epic in the backlog.\n3325\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01RaW7SRJftshaV3GpyJ65tL","session_id":"b101ea9e-2f9e-4377-9c5a-f109fa318b32","uuid":"57960d84-7671-4ffd-8693-ac807629986c","timestamp":"2026-04-03T09:58:02.450Z"}
