 contains real problems, workarounds, bugs, and observations reported by every subagent that ran this session. These are the raw materials for your retrospective — do not ignore them.\n\nCRITICAL: Run `codeharness stats --save` to generate the cost report. Read `_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/cost-report.md` and include cost analysis in the retrospective.\n\nCRITICAL: The session issues log contains `## Token Report` sections from each subagent. Aggregate these to understand WHERE tokens were spent inside subagents (not just the parent). Look for:\n- Which subagent phases had the most tool calls?\n- Which subagents read the same files repeatedly?\n- Which Bash commands produced the largest outputs?\n- What redundant operations were reported?\nInclude this subagent-level breakdown in the cost analysis section.\n\nProduce a retrospective that covers:\n1. **Session summary** — which stories were attempted, their outcomes, time spent\n2. **Issues analysis** — categorize and analyze all issues from the session log:\n   - Bugs discovered during implementation or verification\n   - Workarounds applied (tech debt introduced this session)\n   - Code quality concerns raised by reviewers\n   - Verification gaps (escalated ACs, weak evidence)\n   - Tooling/infrastructure problems (sandbox, permissions, CLI issues)\n3. **Cost analysis** — from the cost report:\n   - Total API-equivalent cost this sprint\n   - Cost per phase (which phases are most expensive?)\n   - Cost per story (which stories cost the most and why?)\n   - Wasted spend (no-op sessions, failed verifications, retries)\n   - Cost optimization opportunities\n4. **What went well** — stories completed, bugs fixed, process improvements\n5. **What went wrong** — failures, blockers, stuck stories, wasted iterations\n6. **Lessons learned** — patterns to repeat or avoid\n7. **Action items** — concrete next steps\n\nWrite the retrospective to _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/session-retro-2026-04-03.md. If a session retro for today already exists, append to it with a `---` separator and timestamp.\n\nDo NOT ask the user any questions — proceed autonomously.\nDo NOT run git commit. Do NOT run git add. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.","agentId":"ada4b9aafcfb29e06","agentType":"general-purpose","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Retrospective written to `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/session-retro-2026-04-03.md` (appended with `---` separator after the existing Session 9 retro).\n\n**Summary of what was produced:**\n\n- **Session 10, Iteration 10** retrospective covering story **12-3-driver-health-check-at-workflow-start**\n- **Epic 12 is now complete** (3/3 stories done)\n- **Sprint progress:** 37/47 stories (78.7%), Epics 1-12 done\n\n**Key findings:**\n- Code review caught a **HIGH timer leak** (`setTimeout` never cleared) and a **MEDIUM AC violation** (timeout error reported wrong drivers). Both fixed in-session.\n- 75 total tool calls — 27% more than 12-2's 59 because this story integrates with a central module (workflow-engine.ts) rather than adding an isolated file\n- **AGENTS.md finally fixed** after 15 sessions — action #3 closed\n- `codeharness stats --save` remains broken (no session-logs dir)\n- Estimated wasted spend: ~$1.00 (redundant file reads, duplicate test runs, proof format mismatch)\n- 7 action items carried forward, 5 new items logged"}],"totalDurationMs":124367,"totalTokens":35118,"totalToolUseCount":18,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3750,"cache_read_input_tokens":31042,"output_tokens":325,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":3750},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
